summary:
Imagine.
Second post credit scene after Endgame.
You see the Avengers compound. A cab is stopping at the door. The radio plays...
body:
Imagine.

Second post credit scene after Endgame.

You see the Avengers compound. A cab is stopping at the door. The radio plays “Reunited” by Peaches & Herb. Dopinder walks out and takes two suitcases full of spider-man stickers from the trunk. He gets into the car again.

The cab leaves and we see a pair of beautiful legs wrapped in red. The legs enter the compound.

Camera slowly goes up. We see Deadpool. He is wearing a Mickey Mouse hat and an Avengers t-shirt. He drops the suitcases and looks around. He shouts/sings: “Honey? I’m home”.

Screen goes black. A phrase appears.

The Marvel family will return.

Reunited plays in the background.

@markruffalo can you get this to Ryan Reynolds and the Russo brothers, please? 😂

summary: Miles is not an orphan raised by his elderly Aunt in Queens. He is not a depressed and bullied nerd whose friends don’t really...
body:
Miles Doing his best Ferris Bueller impression

Miles is not an orphan raised by his elderly Aunt in Queens. He is not a depressed and bullied nerd whose friends don’t really like him. And the latest issue of Almed’s run exemplifies this aspect.

Judge gets the idea to sneak out and go to Brooklyn Muesem to see the Brooklyn Rappers Hip-hop expo where they have note books of prolific rappers on display.

Under Bendis’s Judge was just a kid who used to share a dorm with Miles and Ganke but got sick of the lies and secrets the two were keeping from him and moved out. Almed seems to reinsert him and a bit more characterization that Judge is this artsy Haitian(yes he is confirmed Haitian) who wants to be a poet. The universe switch retconned him knowing about Miles identity and the writer switch retconned him ever giving a shit.

Then there is assistant Principal Lyle Dutcher. The antagonist of the issue.

He thinks Miles is a no good sneak and thrives a busting him sneaking out. Granted, he is right this time but the world building in this issue shows that Miles is what we already suspected. He is a good kid and well-liked by everyone. Teachers like him and students like him although they spread rumors about why he always sneaks out when he is not supposed to.

But the focus on this issue is the relationship between Miles and Barbara, whose last name is either changed or Almed messed up. Judge calls her Miss Gonzales when her name is Barbara Rodriguez. We learn a lot about her and what she is like. We learn that she is devious and fun loving as she coordinated with Judge beforehand to convince Miles to sneak out.

We learn that she is an aspiring rapper which gave more reason why she would be interested in going to the exhibit outside of just hanging out with Miles.

And she totally knows that Miles is Spider-Man.

Regardless this issue was fun but also needed. Miles needed his supporting cast expounded upon outside of Ganke who took a break this issue due to an ear infection. Not many people know of these two and as long as Almed is holding the pen, you will.

@ubernegro

Oh yeah so I am going to be focusing on the Champions-verse(what I call the books associated with the group) and Gwen Stacy. I find myself reading those anyways so… For Dc, I am just waiting for Batman and the Outsiders because it has Cass and it has Duke. That is all I am here for really.

So Champions-verse:

Miles Morales: Spider-Man

The Magnificent Ms. Marvel

Unstoppable Wasp

Ironheart

Champions

Amadeus new book coming next month I think.

And for Dc it is Teen Titans, Young Justice and Batman and the Outsiders. I do read the former two but don’t write about them because I am not too sure what is going on in Young Justice and Teen Titans is annoying because Damian.
